description: RrcInactiveProfile:  This table stores Radio Resource Control (RRC) inactive profile configurations for specific cells at a particular point in time.  `dateTime`: Timestamp of the data record; `Area_Name`: Name of the geographic area; `CellId`: Unique identifier of the cell; `Id2`: Secondary cell identifier (possibly redundant with CellId); `Id3`:  An additional identifier (likely categorical); `Id4`:  Another identifier, potentially indicating a profile type; `vsDataType`: Data type identifier; `vsDataFormatVersion`: Version of the data format; `RrcInactiveProfile.rrcInactiveProfileId`:  Specific ID of the RRC inactive profile configuration.
queries: Show me all RrcInactiveProfile entries for Area_Name 'Downtown' where `vsDataFormatVersion` is 2.0.
What is the `RrcInactiveProfile.rrcInactiveProfileId` for CellId 12345 at dateTime '2024-10-27 10:00:00'?
Retrieve all distinct `Id4` values from RrcInactiveProfile for `vsDataType` = 'LTE'.
Find the latest dateTime entry for each unique `CellId` in the RrcInactiveProfile table.
Give me the count of RrcInactiveProfile records where `Id3` = 'TypeA' and `Area_Name` = 'Suburbia' between '2024-10-26' and '2024-10-28'.
